This repository builds privately distributed WordPress plugins.

Follow WordPress plugin architecture, security, lifecycle, portability, and admin conventions by default.

The only standing exception to wordpress.org-style behavior is approved private-distribution operational reporting.

Never broaden that exception without a documented decision.

Prefer stable contracts, deterministic behavior, and maintainable code over cleverness.

Do not introduce hidden behavior.

Explain architectural tradeoffs before implementing major changes.
